benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/paymentMethods - Retrieve account payment methods

covered: Valid Request scenarios for basic retrieval and various query parameters (TC01–TC07)
Empty response when account has no payment methods (TC08)

Error handling coverage: 404 for non-existent account (TC09), 400 for invalid accountId (TC10), 400 for invalid audit value (TC12), 400 for SQL injection in accountId (TC17), 400/422 for XSS in pluginProperty (TC18)
Combination and filtering coverage across all query parameters: withPluginInfo (TC02), includedDeleted (TC03), pluginProperty (TC04), audit (TC05/TC06), and full combination (TC07)
Deleted vs active visibility when includedDeleted=true (TC03)
Handling of large datasets and performance expectation (TC14)
Recovery from transient dependency failures (TC19) and integration/plugin service unavailability (TC22)
Regression coverage: pluginInfo presence (TC20) and backward compatibility/no-query-params (TC21)
gaps: Pagination handling for large datasets is not explicitly tested
Caching behavior and headers (ETag, Cache-Control) are not tested
Rate limiting/throttling behavior is not tested
403 Forbidden / insufficient permissions scenarios are not tested
Broader security tests beyond SQLi/XSS (e.g., header-based or other input vectors) are not covered
Scenario for explicit 204/no-content or other nuanced API contract variations could be covered
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests (page size, page tokens, total count) to verify correct behavior with large result sets
Add caching tests to verify ETag/Cache-Control headers and client-side caching implications
Add rate limiting tests to ensure the service handles bursts without failure
Add 403 Forbidden scenario coverage to validate proper permission handling
Expand security test coverage to include additional vectors beyond SQL injection and basic XSS, and validate input sanitization more broadly
Consider adding a dedicated test to verify API contract stability without query params across multiple versions (further strengthening TC21)
